<http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12122>
    dc:creator "Juřičková, Lucie", "Korábek, Ondřej", "Petrusek, Adam" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Resurrecting Helix straminea, a forgotten escargot with trans-Adriatic distribution: first insights into the genetic variation within the genus Helix (Gastropoda: Pulmonata)" ;
    bibo:endPage "91" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2014-03-20" ;
    bibo:startPage "72" ;
    bibo:volume "171" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720496>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720502>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720504> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720496>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Comparison of types of (A) Helix lucorum (neotype, Zoological Museum Copenhagen) and (B) H. straminea (probable syntype, MHNG 18135)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4720496/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720502>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Conchological variability of Helix straminea and similar taxa; only individuals not previously depicted elsewhere are included. A, H. straminea, central Italy, Ripe south of Ascoli Piceno (SMF 341626); B, H. straminea, central Albania, Lis in Dibër county (SMF 341628); C, H. straminea, north-eastern Macedonia, Žirovnica (SMF 341613); D, H. vladika, south-eastern Serbia, Trgovište near Knjaževac (SMF 341629); E, H. vladika, eastern Montenegro, Gusinje (SMF 341615); F, H. pelagonesica vardarica, south-eastern Macedonia, environs of Udovo (paratype of H. vardarica, ZMB 90338)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4720502/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4720504>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Distribution of Helix straminea and conchologically similar taxa: H. vladika, and the three H. pelagonesica subspecies; own collections and unpublished collections of ZMB, SMF, MHNG, and NMBE (triangles), online photographs (diamonds) and published records (circles) based on Wohlberedt (1907, 1909), Pavlovic´ (1912), Knipper (1939), Urban´ ski (1970), Giusti (1971), Dhora & Welter-Schultes (1996), Manganelli et al. (2005), and Welter-Schultes (2012). Red symbols indicate localities with molecular data, and the dashed line separates genetically analysed Balkan populations assigned to the straminea and vladika clades in Figure 2. Type localities of the respective species and subspecies are indicated by white circles. Exact positions of some type localities and the locality on Euboea island are not known." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4720504/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

